{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17603734","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17603734"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T12:42:20+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T12:42:20+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15776"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"15776","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/15776"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.15,0.27,0.46,0.08,0.04]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"8467"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"115242"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"8467","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/8467"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15776"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"97250"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"4934"},{"type":"tags","id":"4941"},{"type":"tags","id":"4942"},{"type":"tags","id":"7071"},{"type":"tags","id":"7415"},{"type":"tags","id":"7416"},{"type":"tags","id":"10560"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"20359"},{"type":"contributions","id":"20361"},{"type":"contributions","id":"48800"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"115242","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/115242"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EThe ductus deferens is a key conduit within the male reproductive tract.\u003Cbr\u003EConsider its course, structure, and function.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following best describes the ductus deferens?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Enters the abdomen through the superficial inguinal ring","Forms the ejaculatory duct at the apex of the prostate","Transports and stores sperm","Measures 45 cm with thin muscular walls","Passes inferior to the urethra in the pelvis"],"correctOptions":[2],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe ductus deferens (vas deferens) is a thick-walled muscular tube that carries sperm from the epididymis towards the ejaculatory duct and can store sperm within its ampulla. It traverses the inguinal canal as a component of the spermatic cord and \u003Cstrong\u003Eenters the abdomen through the deep inguinal ring\u003C/strong\u003E, then courses towards the pelvis to join the duct of the seminal vesicle.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EEnters the abdomen through the superficial inguinal ring\u003C/strong\u003E \u2013 incorrect; the superficial ring is the exit of the inguinal canal, while the ductus deferens enters the abdominal cavity through the deep ring.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EForms the ejaculatory duct at the apex of the prostate\u003C/strong\u003E \u2013 incorrect; the ejaculatory duct is formed near the base of the prostate when the ductus deferens joins the seminal vesicle duct, and opens into the prostatic urethra.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ETransports and stores sperm\u003C/strong\u003E \u2013 correct; peristaltic contraction of its robust smooth muscle wall propels sperm during ejaculation, and the ampulla serves as a storage site.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EMeasures 45 cm with thin muscular walls\u003C/strong\u003E \u2013 incorrect; it is approximately 30 cm long and has a characteristic thick, trilaminar smooth muscle wall.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EPasses inferior to the urethra in the pelvis\u003C/strong\u003E \u2013 incorrect; it passes superior to the urethra before converging with the seminal vesicle duct.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":null,"learningPoints":["The ductus deferens stores and conveys sperm from the epididymis to the ejaculatory duct","The ductus deferens enters the abdominal cavity via the deep inguinal ring","The ductus deferens is about 30 cm long and has a thick, trilaminar smooth muscle wall"],"references":["Gurung P, Yetiskul E, Jialal I. Physiology, Male Reproductive System. [Updated 2023 May 1]. In: StatPearls [Internet]. Treasure Island (FL): StatPearls Publishing; 2024 Jan-. Available from: https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/books/NBK538429/","Ansell, I. D. (2012). Atlas of male reproductive pathology (Vol. 10). Springer Science \u0026 Business Media","Koslov DS, Andersson KE. Physiological and pharmacological aspects of the vas deferens-an update. Front Pharmacol. 2013 Aug 22;4:101. doi: 10.3389/fphar.2013.00101. PMID: 23986701; PMCID: PMC3749770."]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"97250"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15776"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"97250","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/97250"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-09-23T10:30:39+09:30","updatedAt":"2025-09-23T10:32:32+09:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"8467"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"115242"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"71","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/71"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Junior","synonyms":null,"description":"Suitable for a junior, pre-clinical medical student","position":0,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"6"}},"heading":{"data"